.TH "add_one_rx_buf" 9 "add_one_rx_buf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
add_one_rx_buf \- add a packet buffer to a free-buffer list
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" add_one_rx_buf
.BI "(void *va "  ","
.BI "unsigned int len "  ","
.BI "struct rx_desc *d "  ","
.BI "struct rx_sw_desc *sd "  ","
.BI "unsigned int gen "  ","
.BI "struct pci_dev *pdev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "va" 12
buffer start VA
.IP "len" 12
the buffer length
.IP "d" 12
the HW Rx descriptor to write
.IP "sd" 12
the SW Rx descriptor to write
.IP "gen" 12
the generation bit value
.IP "pdev" 12
the PCI device associated with the adapter

Add a buffer of the given length to the supplied HW and SW Rx
descriptors.
